<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New record: East Rhodopes, Bryagovets vill., 06.04.2013, 7 q. in a nest of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1798" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Plagiolepis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plagiolepis pygmaea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Plagiolepis pygmaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Latreille, 1798), leg. ALG; Ograzhden Mt., Drakata vill., 09.09.2021, 6 q. in a nest of 
<taxonomicName genus="Pl." lsidName="Pl. pygmaea" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="pygmaea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Pl. pygmaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, leg. ALG. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
