<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
First record for Bulgaria. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Staercke" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Plagiolepis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plagiolepis xene" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xene">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Plagiolepis xene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rare workerless inquiline in nests of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1798" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Plagiolepis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plagiolepis pygmaea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Plagiolepis pygmaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Its distribution range covers southern and central Europe to Anatolia.
</paragraph>
